The paper deals with a graph problem involving demands and connectivity, which suggests it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of demand functions and vertex-disjoint paths suggests it could be in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), while the focus on graph connectivity and the use of approximation algorithms suggests it could be in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The mention of placing servers or warehouses also suggests it could be in cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
